\left(1 + \frac{x}{n}\right)^n
\frac{x^k}{k!}
   (a + b)^n = \sum_{k=0}^n \binom{n}{k} a^k b^{n-k} \text{ where } \binom{n}{k} = \frac{n!}{k!(n-k)!} 
   \left(1 + \frac{x}{n}\right)^n = \sum_{k=0}^n \frac{n!}{n^kk!(n-k)!}x^k   = \sum_{k=0}^n \frac{n(n-1)\ldots(n-k+1)}{n^k} \frac{x^k}{k!} \text{.} 
   \frac{n(n-1)\ldots(n-k+1)}{n^k} \approx 1 \text{.} 
